es.tid.rsvp.constructs

Class SenderDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.tid.rsvp.constructs.RSVPConstruct
      • es.tid.rsvp.constructs.SenderDescriptor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RSVPElement
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SenderDescriptorTE

    public class SenderDescriptor
extends RSVPConstruct

    Represents a Sender Descriptor construct, as defined in RFC 2205.

    The format of a Path message is as follows:

    • <Path Message> ::= <Common Header> [ <INTEGRITY> ] <SESSION> <RSVP_HOP> <TIME_VALUES> [ <POLICY_DATA> ... ] [ <sender descriptor> ]
    • <sender descriptor> ::= <SENDER_TEMPLATE> <SENDER_TSPEC> [ <ADSPEC> ]
    Author:
    Fernando Munoz del Nuevo
